dreisoft.tresos.guidedconfig.api.memento

Class AbstractMementoOperation

  • java.lang.Object
    • dreisoft.tresos.guidedconfig.api.memento.AbstractMementoOperation

  • public abstract class AbstractMementoOperation
extends java.lang.Object
    AbstractMementoOperations are used by the MementoOperationHandler to modify a memento model. To enable Undo/Redo support for custom operations, a subclass of AbstractMementoOperation can be executed via the MementoOperationHandler (within a transaction) by calling MementoOperationHandler.executeOperation(AbstractMementoOperation).
    Since:
    18.0

      • getAbsolutePath

        protected java.lang.String getAbsolutePath(java.lang.String path)
        Make path absolute. If the path is absolute the path is returned. If not the path is interpreted as a relative path to the root memento and the absolute path is returned. An absolute path is only returned if the root mementos memento tree has a root memento (is part of a tree). Else a relative path is returned.
        Parameters:
        path - The path to make absolute
        Returns:
        The absolute path
        Since:
        18.0

      • getAbsolutePaths

        protected java.lang.String[] getAbsolutePaths(java.lang.String[] paths)
        Makes an array of paths absolute. A new array is created and filled with the absolute paths as returned by getAbsolutePath(String).
        Parameters:
        paths - The paths to make absolute
        Returns:
        The absolute paths
        Since:
        18.0

      • getAffectedPaths

        public abstract java.lang.String[] getAffectedPaths()
        Implementors shall return the paths of the mementos affected by the last call to doExecute(IProgressMonitor, APIOperationStatus), doRedo(IProgressMonitor, APIOperationStatus), or doUndo(IProgressMonitor, APIOperationStatus)
        Returns:
        the paths affected by the last call to doExecute(IProgressMonitor, APIOperationStatus), doRedo(IProgressMonitor, APIOperationStatus), or doUndo(IProgressMonitor, APIOperationStatus) .
